<title>BARBADOS: Caribbean to avoid BA strike disruption.</title>
<headline>Caribbean to avoid BA strike disruption.</headline>
<dateline>BRIDGETOWN, Barbados 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>A planned strike by British Airways cabin crew will not affect the Caribbean, the airline said Monday.</p>
<p>BA is the main air link between Britain and its former and remaining colonies in the West Indies.</p>
<p>Cabin crew not involved in the dispute would work on flights scheduled from London's Gatwick Airport to and from Barbados and St.Lucia on Wednesday, and Barbados, Antigua and Grenada on Thursday. No flights are scheduled for Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;We expect it to be business as usual,&quot; BA's South Caribbean manager Elvin Sealy said.</p>
<p>Union officials in London said the first of the cabin crew's planned three-day strikes appeared certain to go ahead after the collapse of the latest round of talks in a dispute over pay and conditions.</p>
